</span><p>Use the <strong>template at the top of this article</strong> to streamline the process of writing your business plan.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=brand-your-courier-service>Brand your courier service.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-a-name-that-reflects-your-brand-values>Choose a name that reflects your brand values.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-choose-a-name-that-reflects-your-brand-and-values-288x288-2020085.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose a name that reflects your brand values."></div></div><p>Your business's name is essential parts of your brand and it needs to make a lasting impact on your target audience. When naming your courier service and choosing a domain name, keep it simple, appropriate, creative, and unique.</p><p>To avoid <strong>trademark infringement,</strong> make sure the name and logo you choose are not similar to ones used by an existing company. If you wittingly or unwittingly use the name of another company, you may be required to change your business name and/or pay damages.</p><p>Follow these simple steps to check if the name and domain you have in mind are available:</p><ul><li>Conduct a Google search to check if anyone else is operating under the same name.</li><li>Check the fictitious name databases at your county clerk's office; their list will include unregistered trademarks used by small companies.</li><li>Get in touch with the state filing office if you plan on registering as an LLC, corporation, or limited partnership; you will need to scan their database to search for similar names.</li><li>Scan the <a
href="https://www.uspto.gov/">federal trademark database</a> to check if your courier service name has not been registered with the USPTO (U.S. Patent and Trademark Office). You can access their free database and click "search," then follow the instructions. You can also use this database to check if the domain you are interested in is available.</li><li>Run a check of your state's trademark database.</li></ul><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
