id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section4" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>4.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=outline-the-finances-you-will-need>Outline the finances you will need.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section4-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=determine-the-overall-costs-of-starting-your-courier-service>Determine the overall costs of starting your courier service.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-determine-the-overall-costs-of-starting-your-courier-service-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Determine the overall costs of starting your courier service."></div></div><p>It may seem like the only essentials required to start a small courier service are the vehicle and the driver, but there are many more expenses. Make a list of everything you think you'll need, and refer to the <a
href="#how-much-does-it-cost-to-start-a-courier-service">estimate prices</a> in the table at the end to get a rough idea of the costs involved.</p><p><strong>Outlined below are some of the expenses you'll want to set aside financing for.</strong></p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section4-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=training>Training.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-training-288x288-20200819-1.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Training."></div></div><p>Most of the drivers you interview should ideally have a commercial driver's license or at least have completed a defensive driving course, but you may want to send them, as well as other workers, for various training workshops that will, for example, improve their efficiency and customer service.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section4-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=buy-fuel-vehicles-and-other-equipment>Buy fuel, vehicles, and other equipment.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-buy-fuel-vehicles-and-other-equipment-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Buy fuel, vehicles, and other equipment."></div></div><p>You will need reliable transport. Whether you decide to purchase vehicles, lease them, or hire drivers who already have their own vehicles, you will need to organize the transport and other equipment like dollies and various office supplies.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section4-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=buy-software>Buy software.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-buy-software-288x288-20200819_2023-09-25-042040_whrq.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Buy software."></div></div><p>You may require a POS system to accept payment for deliveries, as well as fleet management software, hiring software, and a business email address.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section4-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=hire-drivers-and-office-workers>Hire drivers and office workers.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-drivers-and-office-workers-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Hire drivers and office workers."></div></div><p>You will need a team of couriers to make the deliveries on time, as well as an administrative team to respond to queries and manage affairs at the office.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section4-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-supplies>Purchase supplies.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-purchase-supplies-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Purchase supplies."></div></div><p>From pens, invoices and stamps, to spare parts for your vehicles, you will need to source many of the items that keep your courier business running.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section4-step7" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.7&nbsp;</span><h4 id=office-space-and-storage-facilities>Office space and storage facilities.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-office-space-and-storage-facilities-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Office space and storage facilities."></div></div><p>Depending on the size of your company and whether or not you choose to buy the vehicles or hire drivers who already have their own transport, you could <strong>work from a home office</strong>, which would greatly minimize your business costs, but might also limit your expansion potential. <strong>Rent and a safe storage location</strong> might need to be factored into the costs, especially if you have a pick-up facility at the warehouse.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section4-step8" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.8&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-business-license-and-permits>Obtain business license and permits.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-business-licenses-and-permits-288x288-20200819_2020-08-19-105405.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain business license and permits."></div></div><p>Every state has specific licensing and permit requirements that must be met before you can start your courier service. Visit the <a
href="https://www.sba.gov/business-guide/launch-your-business/apply-licenses-permits">U.S. Small Business Administration website</a> to find out more.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section5" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>5.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=secure-funding>Secure funding.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section5-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=ensure-you-have-sufficient-start-up-capital-for-your-courier-service>Ensure you have sufficient start-up capital for your courier service.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-secure-funding-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Ensure you have sufficient start-up capital for your courier service."></div></div><p>Before you begin your courier service, <strong>you will need capital.</strong> Starting small and hiring self-employed drivers who already own cars, instead of permanent staff, could greatly minimize your costs. If you do not have your own fleet or require storage space, you might be able to operate your courier service from home.</p><p><strong>Below are some ways to generate the funding you require to make a success of your courier service.</strong></p><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
