</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Before deciding how to finance your courier service, weigh up the pros and cons of each funding method.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section5-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=bootstrapping>Bootstrapping.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-bootstrapping-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Bootstrapping."></div></div><p>Using your own money and resources to fund your courier service can be a good approach. There are always risks involved with starting a new business, and if you can remove debt from the equation, you automatically minimize those risks.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section5-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-help-from-friends-and-family>Get help from friends and family.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
