</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Even if people don't necessarily donate to your courier service, they could still offer valuable advice and insights. Listen to what your audience has to say and use your crowdfunding platform as a market research tool.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section5-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=approach-angels>Approach angels.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-approach-angels-288x288-20200824.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Approach angels."></div></div><p>You can find angel investors who are willing to provide capital for your courier service. Angel investors can be found online or through industry and top business school networks.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Angel investors can be found through crowdfunding platforms. They can also be friends and family, or mutual business associates. Comb through your existing networks and see what comes up.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section5-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=bank-loans-or-venture-capital>Bank loans or venture capital.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-bank-loans-or-venture-capital-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Bank loans or venture capital."></div></div><p>Before you can secure a loan, your bank will conduct a thorough analysis of both your and your business's financial information, and they will also require collateral. Building a good relationship with your bank through setting up a business account and credit card, might give you an advantage.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section6" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>6.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=decide-on-location>Decide on location.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section6-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=determine-how-much-space-you-need>Determine how much space you need.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-determine-how-much-space-you-need-288x288-20200820.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Determine how much space you need."></div></div><p><strong>Decide if your courier business will be based online or if you will require premises.</strong> If you're doing most of the deliveries yourself or using a network of independent contractors, a home office should be sufficient.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section6-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=find-the-perfect-place-for-your-courier-service-headquarters>Find the perfect place for your courier service headquarters.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-find-the-perfect-place-for-your-courier-service-headquarters-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Find the perfect place for your courier service headquarters."></div></div><p>There are several factors that should be considered when deciding upon a location.</p><p><strong>Some questions you may want to ask yourself include:</strong></p><ul><li>How big should your premises be?</li><li>What kind of security do you require?</li><li>How much will insurance cost?</li><li>How big is the team that will be stationed at the location?</li><li>What kind of amenities do you need at your location?</li><li>Are you in a central location, close to the areas you want to service?</li><li>Are you close to the warehouses you need to collect consignments from?</li><li>Are you close to a train or bus station so workers can arrive in a timely manner?</li><li>Is the neighborhood you are located in safe?</li><li>Will you have a pick-up option? If so, will clients be able to easily find your location?</li><li>Will you have designated pick-up points for clients to collect their orders?</li><li>Are there parking facilities available?</li></ul><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>If a permanent location is not the best fit, maybe shared office space is the way to go? It is a good solution if you would like to test the waters and work from a few flexible locations while you get your courier service off the ground.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section7" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>7.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=take-care-of-the-legal-requirements>Take care of the legal requirements.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section7-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-the-necessary-permits>Obtain the necessary permits.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-the-necessary-permits-and-licenses-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain the necessary permits."></div></div><p>If you're using oversize or overweight vehicles in your business, you'll need a special permit. These permits can be obtained from your state government, but the <a
href="https://ops.fhwa.dot.gov/freight/sw/permit_report/index.htm#obt">U.S. Department of Transportation</a> will redirect you to the correct state office.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section7-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=open-a-business-account-and-obtain-a-credit-card>Open a business account and obtain a credit card.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-open-a-business-account-and-obtain-a-credit-card-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Open a business account and obtain a credit card."></div></div><p>Applying for a small business account and a business credit card will help you keep your business and personal expenses separate. You can use these cards to pay for any business-related costs like licenses, permits, vehicle leasing, fuel, insurance, and taxes. Before applying for a business bank account, you will need to provide proof that your business has been registered.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section7-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=decide-on-a-legal-structure>Decide on a legal structure.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-decide-on-a-legal-structure-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Decide on a legal structure."></div></div><p>For tax purposes, you will have to choose an appropriate legal structure for your courier service. What type of business entity will you be? Setting yourself up as a sole proprietorship is the easiest route as everything will be owned and controlled by you, but operating as a limited liability company (LLC) is a better choice given the size of typical courier services. You can also set yourself up as a limited liability partnership if you have a partner.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Requirements vary by state when forming an LLC. Get a copy of your state's <strong>LLC Articles of Organization Form</strong> by visiting your state's Secretary of State website.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Consider hiring a lawyer to help you establish the legal structure of your business, especially if you've never started a business before.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section7-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=taxes-and-ein>Taxes and EIN.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-get-an-employer-identification-number-288x288-20200817_2023-09-25-044416_lcyk.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Taxes and EIN."></div></div><p>Now that you have chosen a legal structure, registering with the <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/">IRS</a> (Internal Revenue Service) is the next step. The IRS will issue you with your Employer Identification Number (EIN), that you will need if you plan on employing staff to work at your courier service.</p><p>To apply for an EIN, visit the <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/apply-for-an-employer-identification-number-ein-online">IRS's website</a></p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>First-time business owners can do their own taxes using software, or hire a professional to help.</strong> There are many factors that contribute to the price an accountant or tax professional will charge. Businesses who have not kept accurate records of income and expenses could find themselves paying more to have their taxes done. You can sign up with the <a
href="https://nsacct.org/">National Society of Accountants</a> to find out more and to get in touch with an accountant who can provide an accurate quote.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section7-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=licensing-requirements>Licensing requirements.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-licensing-requirements-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Licensing requirements."></div></div><p>The drivers in your employ may need a commercial driver's license. If you will be making some of the deliveries yourself, you should also apply for one. Visit your local DMV website to find out more.</p><p>Every state has its own licensing laws and requirements. Depending on your location, you may need to apply for additional permits. Visit the <a
href="https://www.fmcsa.dot.gov/registration/commercial-drivers-license">United States Department of Transporation's website</a> to find more information and resources.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section7-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=buy-comprehensive-insurance>Buy comprehensive insurance.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-make-sure-your-courier-service-is-covered-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Buy comprehensive insurance."></div></div><p><strong>It is a smart idea for any business to be insured, but it may also be a requirement in your state.</strong> As a courier service, you should consider the following basic insurance needs:</p><ul><li>Business insurance.</li><li>Vehicle insurance.</li><li>General liability insurance.</li><li>Workers' compensation insurance (some states require this even if you don't have employees).</li><li>Equipment insurance.</li><li>Income protection insurance (for circumstances where you are prevented from working).</li><li>Critical illness insurance.</li><li>Business life insurance.</li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Insurance is a vital component of any business.</strong> As the owner of a courier service, you will want to get comprehensive business insurance that covers auto and liability insurance as well. You'll want accident and injury cover, as well as insurance that includes lost or stolen property. Ensure that you are well-protected against any potential lawsuits.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Because driving can be a dangerous occupation that depends on weather conditions, you should definitely consider getting <strong>business interruption insurance. </strong>Business interruption insurance will cover your courier service if regular operations are interrupted because of unforeseen circumstances like the destruction of property or personal injury.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section8" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>8.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=establish-your-rates>Establish your rates.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section8-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=set-up-a-pricing-structure-for-your-courier-service>Set up a pricing structure for your courier service.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-set-up-a-pricing-structure-for-your-courier-service-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Set up a pricing structure for your courier service."></div></div><p><strong>Before you start spending hundreds of dollars on advertising, you need to determine what your services will cost.</strong> Here are a few things you should do:</p><ul><li>Analyze and understand your competitors' delivery rates.</li><li>Conduct research on what clients in the area(s) you are servicing are prepared to pay.</li><li>Make sure your income will cover all running expenses and costs, including tax, toll fees, parking tickets, and vehicle leasing, or vehicle depreciation and maintenance costs.</li><li>Choose a competitive price when your courier service is just starting out.</li></ul></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section8-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=offer-incentives-to-attract-customers>Offer incentives to attract customers.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-offer-incentives-to-attract-customers-288x288-20200820.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Offer incentives to attract customers."></div></div><p>People who have relied on large courier services to get their parcels delivered will need a reason to switch over to your service. Make it worth their while by <strong>offering reduced rates to loyal customers and preparing special packages for big clients</strong>.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>A simple way to build a superior courier service would be to <strong>find out what customers want</strong>. If they need express shipping or after-hours delivery, and you can provide it at a good price, you'll be a step ahead of the competition.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section9" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>9.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=staff-your-courier-service>Staff your courier service.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section9-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=determine-the-number-of-workers-you-need>Determine the number of workers you need.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-determine-the-number-of-workers-you-need-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Determine the number of workers you need."></div></div><p>When you start out, you may only have a few deliveries that you're able to do on your own, but as your business grows, so will the need for more fleet vehicles and staff. Positions you may need to fill include:</p><ul><li>Couriers/drivers.</li><li>Packers.</li><li>Manager(s).</li><li>Customer support staff.</li><li>Security guards.</li><li>Cleaning staff.</li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>GPS has made it easier than ever for couriers to deliver packages, but hiring drivers who know the lay of the land and have a good sense of direction, still has its advantages. Be sure to keep an eye out for these candidates.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section9-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=advertise-jobs>Advertise jobs.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-advertise-jobs-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Advertise jobs."></div></div><p>Use job posting sites, job boards, and social media to get the word out about your new courier service. Be sure to look for candidates who live close to your headquarters, or who are situated near the areas you'll be servicing.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section9-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=train-your-employees>Train your employees.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-train-your-employees-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Train your employees."></div></div><p>The couriers you hire will probably know how to drive, but they will still require training along with your other staff members. Training at a courier service may include:</p><ul><li>Workplace procedures and safety.</li><li>Equipment and vehicle maintenance.</li><li>Customer service training.</li><li>General workplace etiquette.</li><li>Systems training, which may include fleet management software, POS systems, shipping software, CRM, and more.</li></ul></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section10" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>10.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=online-presence-and-marketing>Online presence and marketing.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section10-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=know-who-your-target-audience-is-before-you-start-your-marketing-campaign>Know who your target audience is before you start your marketing campaign.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-know-who-your-target-audience-is-before-you-start-your-marketing-campaign-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Know who your target audience is before you start your marketing campaign."></div></div><p>You would have established your target audience during your market research phase right at the start. <strong>Once you know who your potential clients are, you have a better chance of reaching them.</strong></p><p>There are several ways to market your courier service. Some methods will not cost you a dime, while others can set you back hundreds of dollars. Carefully consider who you need to reach and the channels available to you.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section10-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=use-the-internet>Use the internet.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-use-the-internet-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Use the internet."></div></div><p>It is absolutely free to register your business on LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram, and Twitter.
Using these platforms will help <strong>increase brand visibility</strong> and also allow you to have <strong>meaningful interactions with your clients</strong> and the broader public. There are also free email marketing services you could use to inform clients about upcoming promotions.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section10-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=network-with-key-players>Network with key players.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-network-with-key-players-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Network with key players."></div></div><p>Approach businesses that are likely to require courier services so you can secure long-term clients. Another great way of expanding your client base is to attend events where you can meet potential clients.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section10-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=build-a-website>Build a website.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-build-a-website-288x288-20200817_2023-09-25-050036_onwn.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Build a website."></div></div><p>Having a sleek homepage will increase the credibility of your courier service. It does not have to be anything fancy, just a place where you can list prices, contact information, and where clients can go to track their orders.</p><p>There are some great free options like <a
href="https://wordpress.com/start/user?ref=create-website-lp">WordPress</a> or paid website builders if you require more features or customization.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section10-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=press-release>Press release.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-press-release-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Press release."></div></div><p>This is a great way to communicate information about your new courier service to a news outlet. Choose a winning angle, a catchy heading, and keep it short and sweet. Make sure you've done your research on the website or platform you're submitting your press release to.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section10-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=traditional-advertising>Traditional advertising.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-traditional-advertising-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Traditional advertising."></div></div><p>Printing your name and logo on your courier vehicles is a great way to advertise. Making posters and flyers are also more traditional methods of creating brand awareness. You can have customized merchandise like pens, notepads, and mugs printed with your courier service information, too.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section10-step7" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.7&nbsp;</span><h4 id=referrals>Referrals.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-referrals-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Referrals."></div></div><p>Word of mouth marketing is one of the oldest and most powerful methods of gaining new customers. Providing existing clients with incentives like discounts and freebies can be a good way to get them to recommend your courier service.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-courier-service-section10-step8" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.8&nbsp;</span><h4 id=opening-specials>Opening specials.</h4></div><div
