>\n<li>What kind of security do you require?<\/li>\n<li>How much will insurance cost?<\/li>\n<li>How big is the team that will be stationed at the location?<\/li>\n<li>What kind of amenities do you need at your location?<\/li>\n<li>Are you in a central location, close to the areas you want to service?<\/li>\n<li>Are you close to the warehouses you need to collect consignments from?<\/li>\n<li>Are you close to a train or bus station so workers can arrive in a timely manner?<\/li>\n<li>Is the neighborhood you are located in safe?<\/li>\n<li>Will you have a pick-up option? If so, will clients be able to easily find your location?<\/li>\n<li>Will you have designated pick-up points for clients to collect their orders?<\/li>\n<li>Are there parking facilities available?<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-courier-service#how-to-start-a-courier-service-section6-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-find-the-perfect-place-for-your-courier-service-headquarters-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>If a permanent location is not the best fit, maybe shared office space is the way to go? It is a good solution if you would like to test the waters and work from a few flexible locations while you get your courier service off the ground.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"7","name":"<p>Take care of the legal requirements.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Obtain the necessary permits.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>If you're using oversize or overweight vehicles in your business, you'll need a special permit. These permits can be obtained from your state government, but the <a href=\"https:\/\/ops.fhwa.dot.gov\/freight\/sw\/permit_report\/index.htm#obt\">U.S. Department of Transportation<\/a> will redirect you to the correct state office.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.not